  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Beginning at 1st level, the members of the Hoshimi clan are trained to be specialized hunters of non-human monsters. You gain a +1d4 bonus to <strong>Survival</strong> and <strong>Investigation</strong> Checks made to Track, Research, or otherwise interact or use a Skill Based Actions with <strong>Abberations</strong> and <strong>Monstrosities</strong>. This becomes a 1d6 at 7th level, and 1d8 at 15th.</p><p>Additionally, at the start of each of your turns in combat, you can choose 1 creature you can see other than yourself. That creature becomes your <strong>Hunt Target</strong>. You can only have 1 <strong>Hunt Target</strong>. The chosen creature counts as an <strong>Abberation</strong> or <strong>Monstrosity</strong> (your choice) for the purposes of interacting with Jutsu, Features, and Weapon Seals.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
